  "texts": [
    "TimeViper achieves promising performance for long video understanding across multi-choice video QA, temporal video grounding, and detailed video captioning.",
    "Experimental SetupsImplementation details.",
    "When training attention-based dropping in multi-turn dialogue scenarios, the attention distribution is computed using the last token of the final instruction as the query.",
    "For temporal video grounding data, we incorporate a time-aware prompt [50]: \"The video lasts for {} seconds, and {} frames are uniformly sampled from it.\"",
    "During training, we randomly sample one instruction from a pool of 15 manually constructed task prompts, such as: \"From the video, locate the portion that aligns with the textual query, and output the start and end timestamps in seconds."
